# Default values for Vite environment variables.
# These can be overridden by .env.development, .env.production, .env.local, or system environment variables.

# Define these in your system environment or a .env.local file (which is not committed)
# For example, in your .bashrc, .zshrc, or a .env.local file:
# export CITYLIGHTS_HOST="your_api_host"
# export CITYLIGHTS_PORT="your_api_port"
# export SKIP_TLS="true_or_false" # true for http, false for https

# Vite will use these to populate VITE_API_BASE_URL and VITE_SOCKET_IO_URL if not already set by more specific files.
# The actual construction of VITE_API_BASE_URL and VITE_SOCKET_IO_URL is done in app/config.js
# using the VITE_API_HOST, VITE_API_PORT, and VITE_SKIP_TLS variables.

# Example:
# VITE_APP_NAME="CityLights Default"
# VITE_API_HOST="localhost"
# VITE_API_PORT="3000" # Default API port if not specified by CITYLIGHTS_PORT
# VITE_SKIP_TLS="true" # Default to http if not specified by SKIP_TLS

# Note: VITE_ prefixed variables in this file will be loaded by Vite.
# However, the app/config.js primarily looks for VITE_API_HOST, VITE_API_PORT, and VITE_SKIP_TLS.
# It's recommended to set these via system environment variables or .env.local for actual deployment configurations.
# This file serves more as a template and documentation for required variables.
